JP>In article <lo59597@pro-cynosure.clark.net>,
JP>Barry Herman <barryh@pro-cynosure.clark.net> wrote:
JP>>> Is this calculator programmable enough...
JP>>No, it's not a programmable calculator, but here's what is takes:
JP>><on> <password> <xor> <challenge> <hex> <xor> <password> <dec>

JP>Try this:
JP><on> <password> <hex> <xor> <password> <dec>

JP>Write down the result.  Call that p'

JP>Given a challenge and p':
JP><on> <p'> <xor> <challenge>

JP>will yield the <response>.  To find p' given a challenge and response:
JP><on> <response> <xor> <challenge>

JP>I think this security scheme needs work.

Yeah, you can find p'. But can you find p?  As I said through the mail,
if this scheme is as weak as you say then this should be a trivial task for
you: c = 4550696 r = 105375002  What is p?

Barry (This was not intended as a flame, merely a challenge)


